  "text": "where π represents the amount invested in S. The set A t of admissible strategies on [t, T ] consists of all G-predictable processes π = (π s ) t≤s≤T which satisfy abbreviated by 'of P -class (D)'. We define V B (and analogously V 0 ) for t ∈ [0, T ] and x t bounded G t -measurable by [CITATION_1] using that (bounded) G t -measurable factors can be pulled out. Thus V B t (x t ) is the maximal expected utility the investor can achieve by starting at time t with initial capital x t , using some admissible strategy π, and paying out B at time T .",
